   "source": [
    "## _Mathematical_ Computation vs. _Mechanical_ Computation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "In a mathematical theorem, working with (idealized) numbers, it is always true that:\n",
    "\n",
    "If \n",
    "\n",
    "$$c = 1/a$$ \n",
    "\n",
    "then \n",
    "\n",
    "$$abc = b.$$\n",
    "\n",
    "In other words, \n",
    "\n",
    "$$(ab)/a = b.$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Let's test whether this is always true in actual computation."
