     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "### Principle 1: Do not compare floating point numbers for equality"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "Two floating point computations that _should_ yield the same result mathematically, may not do so due to rounding error.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, in general, if two numbers should be equal, the relative error of the difference in the floating point should be small.\n",
    "\n",
    "So, instead of asking whether two floating numbers are equal, we should ask whether the relative error of their difference is small."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "1.3877787807814457e-16"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 16,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "r1 = a * b * c\n",
    "r2 = b * c * a\n",
    "np.abs(r1-r2)/r1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "skip"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
